Description: EX3_ECOLI - Also known as xth. Experimental evidence at protein level: Swiss-Prot protein existence level 1. Major apurinic-apyrimidinic endonuclease of E.coli. It removes the damaged DNA at cytosines and guanines by cleaving on the 3'-side of the AP site by a beta-elimination reaction. It exhibits 3'- 5'-exonuclease, 3'-phosphomonoesterase, 3'-repair diesterase and ribonuclease H activities. From Escherichia coli (strain K12).
β-lactamase; bla; confers resistance to ampicillin, carbenicillin, and related antibiotics
transcription terminator for bacteriophage T7 RNA polymerase
bidirectional E. coli tonB-P14 transcription terminator
LacZα fragment of β-galactosidase; lacZ fragment
